{"name": "swh-perfecthash", "metadata": {"name": "swh.perfecthash", "version": "1.3.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": "https://docs.softwareheritage.org/devel/swh-perfecthash/", "dependencies": ["cffi"], "summary": "Software Heritage Perfect Hash", "upload_time": 1718031446}, "documentation": ["# Perfect Hash table for Software Heritage Object Storage\n\nA perfect hash table for software heritage object storage.\n\n## Build dependencies\n\nThis packages uses cffi to build the wrapper around the cmph minimal perfect\nhashmap library. To build the binary extension, in addition to the python\ndevelopment tools, you will need cmph, gtest and valgrind. On de Debian\nsystem, you can install these using:\n\n```shell\nsudo apt install build-essential python3-dev libcmph-dev libgtest-dev valgrind lcov\n```\n\nThen you should be able to build the binary extension:\n\n```shell\npython -m build\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "docs.conf", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "setup", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python3", "Copyright (C) 2021-2023  The Software Heritage developers", "See the AUTHORS file at the top-level directory of this distribution", "License: GNU General Public License version 3, or any later version", "See top-level LICENSE file for more information"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.build", "documentation": ["Copyright (C) 2021-2024  The Software Heritage developers", "See the AUTHORS file at the top-level directory of this distribution", "License: GNU General Public License version 3, or any later version", "See top-level LICENSE file for more information"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "swh.perfecthash.build.ffibuilder", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.build.library_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.build.extra_compile_args", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.build.bundled_cmph", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.tests", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "conftest", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "conftest.pytest_addoption", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "parser", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash", "documentation": ["Copyright (C) 2021-2022  The Software Heritage developers", "See the AUTHORS file at the top-level directory of this distribution", "License: GNU General Public License version 3, or any later version", "See top-level LICENSE file for more information"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "swh.perfecthash.Key", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "swh.perfecthash.ShardCreator", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "swh.perfecthash.ShardCreator.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "object_count", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a Shard.\n\nThe file at `path` will be truncated if it already exists.\n\n`object_count` must match the number of objects that will be added\nusing the {meth}`write` method. A `RuntimeError` will be raised\non {meth}`finalize` in case of inconsistencies.\n\nIdeally this should be done using a `with` statement, as such:\n\n```python\nwith ShardCreator(\"shard\", len(objects)) as shard:\n    for key, object in objects.items():\n        shard.write(key, object)\n```\n\nOtherwise, {meth}`prepare`, {meth}`write` and {meth}`finalize` must be\ncalled in sequence.\n\nArgs:\n\n: path: path to the Shard file or device that will be written.\n  object_count: number of objects that will be written to the Shard.\n"]}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.ShardCreator.__enter__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "ShardCreator", "xref": {"fqname": "swh.perfecthash.ShardCreator", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.ShardCreator.__exit__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exc_type", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Type", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "BaseException", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.BaseException", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "exc_val", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "BaseException", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.BaseException", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "exc_tb", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "TracebackType", "xref": {"fqname": "types.TracebackType", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.ShardCreator.__del__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.ShardCreator._destroy", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.ShardCreator.prepare", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Initialize the shard.\n\nRaises:\n    RuntimeError: something went wrong while creating the Shard."]}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.ShardCreator.finalize", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Finalize the Shard.\n\nWrite the index and the perfect hash table\nthat will be used to find the content of the objects from\ntheir key.\n\nRaises:\n: RuntimeError: if the number of written objects does not match `object_count`,\n\n  : or if something went wrong while saving.\n"]}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.ShardCreator.write", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": {"name": "Key", "xref": {"fqname": "Key", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "object", "type": {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Add the key/object pair to the Read Shard.\n\nArgs:\n    key: the unique key associated with the object.\n    object: the object\n\nRaises:\n    ValueError: if the key length is wrong, or if enough objects\n        have already been written.\n    RuntimeError: if something wrong happens when writing the object."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Shard", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "swh.perfecthash.Shard.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Open an existing Read Shard.\n\nArgs:\n    path: path to an existing Read Shard file or device"]}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Shard.__del__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Shard.close", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Shard.__enter__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Shard", "xref": {"fqname": "swh.perfecthash.Shard", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Shard.__exit__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exc_type", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Type", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "BaseException", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.BaseException", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "exc_val", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "BaseException", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.BaseException", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "exc_tb", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "TracebackType", "xref": {"fqname": "types.TracebackType", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Shard.key_len", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Shard.lookup", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": {"name": "Key", "xref": {"fqname": "Key", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Fetch the object matching the key in the Read Shard.\n\nFetching an object is O(1): one lookup in the index to obtain\nthe offset of the object in the Read Shard and one read to get\nthe payload.\n\nArgs:\n    key: the key associated with the object to retrieve.\n\nReturns:\n   the object as bytes.\n\nRaises:\n   KeyError: the object has been deleted\n   RuntimeError: something went wrong during lookup"]}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Shard.delete", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": {"name": "Key", "xref": {"fqname": "Key", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Open the Shard file and delete the given key.\n\nThe object size and data will be overwritten by zeros. The Shard\nfile size and offsets are not changed for safety.\n\nArgs:\n    key: the key associated with the object to retrieve.\n\nRaises:\n   KeyError: the object has been deleted\n   RuntimeError: something went wrong during lookup"]}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Shard._delete", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": {"name": "Key", "xref": {"fqname": "Key", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Files storing objects indexed with a perfect hash table.\n\nThis class allows creating a Read Shard by adding key/object pairs\nand looking up the content of an object when given the key.\n\nThis class can act as a context manager, like so:\n\n```python\nwith Shard(\"shard\") as shard:\n    return shard.lookup(key)\n```\n"]}], "exports": [{"name": "swh.perfecthash.cast", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.cast", "project": null}}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.FFI", "xref": {"fqname": "cffi.FFI", "project": "cffi"}}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.lib", "xref": {"fqname": "swh.perfecthash._hash_cffi.lib", "project": null}}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.NewType", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.NewType", "project": null}}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": null}}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.TracebackType", "xref": {"fqname": "types.TracebackType", "project": null}}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.Type", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Type", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.tests.test_hash", "documentation": ["Copyright (C) 2021-2022  The Software Heritage developers", "See the AUTHORS file at the top-level directory of this distribution", "License: GNU General Public License version 3, or any later version", "See top-level LICENSE file for more information"], "functions": [{"name": "swh.perfecthash.tests.test_hash.setrlimit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "swh.perfecthash.tests.test_hash.populated_shard_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tmp_path", "type": null, "default": null}